Sentencas: The higher cost of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) compared with the cost of conventional energy conversion devices has greatly hindered their wide application.
Titulo: Impregnated LaCo0.3Fe0.67Pd0.03O3-δ as a promising electrocatalyst for symmetrical intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The symmetrical SOFCs that use identical material as both cathode and anode can greatly reduce the fabrication cost.
Titulo: Impregnated LaCo0.3Fe0.67Pd0.03O3-δ as a promising electrocatalyst for symmetrical intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The key point for the development of symmetrical SOFCs is to find a promising electrode catalyst.
Titulo: Impregnated LaCo0.3Fe0.67Pd0.03O3-δ as a promising electrocatalyst for symmetrical intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, we report a LaCo0.3Fe0.67Pd0.03O3-delta (LCFPd) material with superior catalytic activity under both oxidizing and reducing atmospheres due to the slight Pd-doping.
Titulo: Impregnated LaCo0.3Fe0.67Pd0.03O3-δ as a promising electrocatalyst for symmetrical intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An LCFPd-infiltrated Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) electrode possesses competitive oxygen reduction activity compared with a Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) cathode and exhibits even better fuel oxidation activity than the state-of-the-art Ni-SDC composite anode.
Titulo: Impregnated LaCo0.3Fe0.67Pd0.03O3-δ as a promising electrocatalyst for symmetrical intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the superiority of LCFPd is demonstrated through the high and stable power outputs that can be obtained from a symmetrical SOFC with an LCFPd-based electrode as both cathode and anode.
Titulo: Impregnated LaCo0.3Fe0.67Pd0.03O3-δ as a promising electrocatalyst for symmetrical intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
